1
00:00:00,131 --> 00:00:01,692
Let's talk about the prerequisites.

2
00:00:02,092 --> 00:00:05,133
You do not need to be a stock market expert to do well in this course.

3
00:00:05,813 --> 00:00:07,954
The students from different backgrounds are welcome.

4
00:00:08,574 --> 00:00:10,255
If you are new to finance, that is fine.

5
00:00:10,955 --> 00:00:15,117
Many students become interested in finance after they start working with the data.

6
00:00:16,147 --> 00:00:18,108
We'll use Python throughout the course.

7
00:00:18,768 --> 00:00:24,589
Many assignments will require you to write code, test your work, debug problems.

8
00:00:25,390 --> 00:00:28,571
We'll move at a steady pace, so you should be ready to practice.

9
00:00:29,411 --> 00:00:33,232
We'll also use coding agents to help us write and improve code.

10
00:00:33,912 --> 00:00:39,934
These tools can be very helpful, but you still need to understand the basics of coding to use them well.

11
00:00:40,734 --> 00:00:47,435
At minimum, you should be familiar with Python basics such as functions, loops, conditionals, and basic data structures.

12
00:00:48,115 --> 00:00:54,277
If Python is new to you, plan to spend extra time early in the course getting comfortable with it.

13
00:00:54,897 --> 00:00:58,837
I have also added resources on the course website to help you get started.

14
00:00:59,438 --> 00:01:06,639
The finance concepts will build over time, but strong programming skills will help you keep up from the beginning.

